message.content:
cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the formalisation of security properties of crypto-based components.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper uses Isabelle/HOL+Isar to specify and verify the composition properties of the components.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with the formalisation of components and their properties.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with the verification of software components.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with the formalisation of security properties and their proofs.
